<br>
The Second Amendment isn't there to protect hunters or whatnot. It's meant to allow the people to stay armed as a protection against tyranny.<br>
<br>
If the Government registers all the weapons, and knows where they all are, it's a very simple matter to confiscate them if and when the tyranny comes. And I don't know about you, but my ancestors felt rather strongly on the topic of tyranny. And I agree with their take on this. [As an aside, none of my weapons are registered, or fingerprinted, or findable without a rather serious and complete search of my premises. None of which was illegal at the time.]<br>
<br>
Until you understand the concept, you will never understand why those of us who treasure the Second Amendment refuse to accept any dilution of the right to keep and bear arms. It's to protect our FREEDOM, not our ability to plink cans or wack elk.<br>
